In this implementation, we use two stacks (`stack1` and `stack2`) to implement the queue. The `enqueue` operation simply adds an item to the end of `stack1`. The `dequeue` operation checks if `stack2` is empty, and if so, it pops all items from `stack1` and pushes them onto `stack2`. Then it pops the top item from `stack2` and returns it. The `peek` operation is similar to `dequeue`, but it doesn't pop the item from `stack2`. The `is_empty` and `size` operations simply check the lengths of `stack1` and `stack2`.
